I"U<p>The increased <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/physical-and-conceptual-spaces-are-coded-in-the-same-region">contact surface</a> of herb particles in boiling water when making tea leads to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/symbols-diffuse-in-latent-space">increased diffusion</a>. Similarly, diverse blended societies lead to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-seeks-homeostasis">less conflict</a>. Is the increased contact surface the cause, or an effect of a different <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-seeks-homeostasis">homeostasis</a>?</p>
